Installation on Windows

1. download and install python:
  - 64 bit version: https://www.python.org/ftp/python/2.7.13/python-2.7.13.amd64.msi
  - 32 bit version: https://www.python.org/ftp/python/2.7.13/python-2.7.13.msi

2. Download https://bootstrap.pypa.io/get-pip.py, being careful to save it as a .py file rather than .txt.
Then, run it from the command prompt:

python.exe get-pip.py

You possibly need an administrator command prompt to do this. Follow Start a Command Prompt as an Administrator (Microsoft TechNet).

3. open command prompt and execute this commands:

cd c:\Python27\Scripts
pip.exe install beautifulsoup4
pip.exe install configparser

4. download and install GIT from http://git-scm.com/download/win

5. open mingw64 command prompt and execute this commands to download this project:

cd /c
git clone https://github.com/bercob/hobby_prices.git

6. make a copy of ini/credentials.example.ini to ini/credentials.ini and fill the credentials

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Usage: ./update_prices.py <ini file path>

update prices

author: Balogh Peter <bercob@gmail.com>

Options:
  -h, --help     show this help message and exit
  -v, --version  get version
